Discovery
*********

The local root is accepted only when `Data/Map_Sym.txt' is readable below
that root.  No network locations are probed.

Candidates are checked in this order:

1. `common-lisp-hyperspec-root', if it is already a `file://' URL.

2. The `:hyperspec' entry from `get-directory', typically configured in
   `~/directories.txt'.

3. The Quicklisp installed-system record:
   `~/quicklisp/dists/quicklisp/installed/systems/clhs.txt'.

4. The Quicklisp convenience symlink:
   `~/quicklisp/HyperSpec/'.

5. Common packaged locations:
   `/opt/local/share/doc/lisp/lisp-hyperspec-7.0/HyperSpec/'
   `/usr/share/doc/hyperspec/HyperSpec/'
   `/usr/share/doc/hyperspec/'
   `/usr/local/share/doc/cl/HyperSpec/'
   `/usr/local/html/local/lisp/www.lispworks.com/documentation/HyperSpec/'
   `/data/lisp/hyperspec-7.0/HyperSpec/'
   `/opt/local/share/doc/lisp/HyperSpec-7-0/HyperSpec/'

6. Quicklisp CLHS wrapper versions matching:
   `~/quicklisp/dists/quicklisp/software/clhs-*/HyperSpec-7-0/HyperSpec/'.

When a root is found, `common-lisp-hyperspec-root' is set to its `file://'
URL and `*hyperspec-path*' is set to the filesystem directory.


