Troubleshooting
***************

Error: "Local CLHS not found"
     Install a local copy with `M-x pjb-clhs-install-quicklisp', install an
     OS package such as MacPorts `lisp-hyperspec', or configure the
     `:hyperspec' directory entry so that it points to a HyperSpec directory
     containing `Data/Map_Sym.txt'.

Error: "The symbol ... is not defined in Common Lisp"
     The local CLHS was found, but the requested name is not present in
     `Data/Map_Sym.txt'.  Check spelling or use completion from `M-x clhs'.

Lookup opens the wrong browser
     Set `common-lisp-hyperspec-browser' to the desired `browse-url'
     function before running lookup.

Changing CLHS installations during an Emacs session
     Reset `common-lisp-hyperspec-root', `*hyperspec-path*', and
     `common-lisp-hyperspec-symbols' to nil, then run `M-x clhs' again.
